			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				2 complete outages on the Nameless? I'll admit.. that's pretty lame. I bet the boys and girls at Verant are feeling pretty sheepish right now. Experience for our troubles? Don't be absurd.<BR>
<BR>
Some people weren't even playing during that time.. and they're going to receive free experience for it? No way. By that standard, every character on my roster will receive experience. That's not right.<BR>
<BR>
I got the components for two pieces of totemic (completed the quests, and gave the items to my cousin's shaman) and three bubbles of experience. I'd say it was my most productive few hours ever on this game. However, it makes no sense to whine about refunds or anything like that. The mechanics of it are way too complex to implement. You do one thing, you have to do another, and someone will complain because so and so got too much or they didn't get enough. It's just an unfortunate thing and we need to live with it.<BR>
<BR>
HOWEVER.. if Verant wishes to have more events on the Nameless (I'm sorry.. but our events are far and inbetween, and they suck tremendously) to make up for it, I won't complain!  ;)
				</font>
